#compdef node-dev
# =============================================================================
# node-dev — Felix Gnass's "Restarts your app when files
#            are modified" — a zero-config Node.js
#            file-watcher + auto-restart utility that
#            sits between Node.js's bare `node script.js`
#            and heavier alternatives like nodemon,
#            pm2, or ts-node-dev.  Designed for
#            development-loop workflows where you edit
#            JS/TS source files + want the running
#            process automatically restarted whenever
#            a touched file is saved.  Supports both
#            classic require-based Node modules + ES
#            modules (via dynamic-dedupe + filewatcher
#            integration).
#            Distinguishing from nodemon (cli flag-
#            heavy + config-file-heavy), pm2 (process
#            manager + production focus), ts-node-dev
#            (TypeScript-specific fork), supervisor
#            (older, less maintained), forever (old
#            production process manager), and tsx watch
#            (Bun + ESM-only modern alternative) by:
#              - ZERO-CONFIG WATCH — `node-dev script.js`
#                Just Works.  filewatcher (jaredly's
#                cross-platform fs.watch wrapper)
#                detects source changes; node-dev
#                restarts the script automatically;
#                no `nodemon.json` or watch-pattern
#                config required
#              - DYNAMIC DEDUPE — uses dynamic-dedupe
#                to merge multiple copies of the same
#                module across the require cache;
#                prevents "Module 'X' is loaded twice"
#                bugs that plague long-running watch
#                loops
#              - NODE-NOTIFIER DESKTOP ALERTS — uses
#                mikaelbr/node-notifier for cross-
#                platform desktop notifications when
#                a restart fails (syntax error,
#                exception, etc.); `--notify=false`
#                disables (this is the headline CLI
#                library that closes Axis 34 on the
#                TS-Node side; see taxonomy notes
#                below)
#              - FORK MODE — `--fork` runs the script
#                as a subprocess via Node's
#                child_process.fork instead of cluster
#                worker; isolates crashed scripts
#                from the watcher
#              - GRACEFUL IPC SHUTDOWN — `--graceful_ipc
#                <signal>` sends a configurable signal
#                to the child for graceful shutdown
#                before SIGKILL; useful for cleanup of
#                file handles, sockets, in-progress
#                HTTP requests
#              - VM CONTEXT — `--vm` runs the script
#                in a fresh VM context for each restart;
#                avoids module-cache pollution between
#                restarts
#              - DEBOUNCE — `--debounce <ms>` suppresses
#                cascading restarts when multiple files
#                save quickly (e.g., from build tools
#                like Webpack or esbuild writing many
#                files in succession)
#              - IGNORE PATTERNS — `--ignore <path>`
#                excludes files / directories from the
#                watch set; multiple `--ignore` flags
#                supported
#              - DEPS DEPTH — `--deps <N>` controls how
#                deep node-dev recursively watches the
#                node_modules dependency tree (default
#                0 = no node_modules watching)
#              - POLL MODE — `--poll` switches from
#                native fs.watch (which has reliability
#                issues on macOS + network filesystems)
#                to polling at `--interval <ms>`
#              - CLEAR SCREEN — `--clear` clears the
#                terminal before each restart (like
#                webpack-dev-server's behavior)
#              - TIMESTAMP — `--timestamp <format>`
#                prefixes restart messages with date/
#                time using dateformat
#              - NODE FLAG PASS-THROUGH — node-dev
#                forwards `--require`, `--inspect`,
#                `--inspect-brk`, `--expose_gc`,
#                `--preserve-symlinks`, `--no-warnings`
#                directly to the underlying Node
#                process
#              - RESPAWN — `--respawn` auto-respawns
#                on script exit (even non-error exits);
#                useful for testing long-running
#                process startup
#            Used by: Node.js + TypeScript developers
#            in active development loops, instructors
#            teaching Node.js where rapid feedback
#            matters more than production reliability,
#            JavaScript bootcamps, and anyone running
#            scripts that should restart on save
#            without complex `nodemon` config files.
#
# Author:  Felix Gnass (fgnass on GitHub).  Contributors
#          include Daniel Gasienica + Bjorn Stromberg.
#          License: MIT.  Active development with
#          continuous releases since 2010.
# Source:  https://github.com/fgnass/node-dev
