# CROSS-LANGUAGE CLI LIBRARY TAXONOMY — AXIS 34 CLOSES AT 1/1/1: CROSS-PLATFORM DESKTOP NOTIFICATIONS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This completion **CLOSES AXIS 34 AT 1/1/1** in the cross-language
# CLI library taxonomy: Cross-Platform Desktop Notifications.
#
# Pattern: R725 Rust=89 (rusty-krab-manager/notify-rust → Axis 34
# OPENS) → R726 Go=89 (updo/gen2brain-beeep) → R727 TS-Node=89
# (node-dev/node-notifier → Axis 34 CLOSES AT 1/1/1 THIS) → R728
# 114th language.
#
# WHY mikaelbr/node-notifier IS A DISTINCTIVE AXIS-34 TS-NODE CHOICE:
#
#   node-notifier (mikaelbr/node-notifier on GitHub, npm package
#   `node-notifier`) is Mikael Brevik's "A Node.js module for
#   sending notifications on native Mac, Windows and Linux" — the
#   dominant Node.js cross-platform desktop notification library.
#   Distinguishing characteristics:
#     1. CROSS-PLATFORM — Linux (notify-send via libnotify), macOS
#        (terminal-notifier wrapper, falling back to AppleScript),
#        Windows (WinRT toast via PowerShell, falling back to
#        balloon notifications), with explicit per-platform reporter
#        classes
#     2. PLATFORM REPORTERS — `NotificationCenter` (macOS), `Growl`
#        (cross-platform legacy), `NotifySend` (Linux),
#        `WindowsBalloon` (older Windows), `WindowsToaster`
#        (Windows 10+ WinRT), `Notifier` (auto-selects best
#        platform);  developers can pick a specific reporter or
#        let auto-select choose
#     3. RICH NOTIFICATION CONTENT — title, message, icon path
#        (PNG/JPEG), sound (true/false or specific sound name),
#        wait-for-user-click, timeout, urgency (low/normal/critical),
#        actions (clickable buttons; macOS + Windows 10+ only)
#     4. CALLBACK + EVENT API — `notifier.notify({...}, callback)`
#        AND `notifier.on('click', handler)` for response handling;
#        accommodates both promise-style + event-emitter usage
#     5. TERMINAL-NOTIFIER BUNDLED — ships with vendored binary of
#        Julian Gruber's terminal-notifier (macOS native
#        notification CLI) so end users don't need to install
#        anything separately
#     6. ~6,700+ STARS on mikaelbr/node-notifier
#     7. ~12M+ WEEKLY NPM DOWNLOADS — extremely widely used in
#        the Node.js + TypeScript ecosystem
#     8. WIDE BUILD-TOOL ADOPTION — used by Jest (test framework
#        notifications), Karma (browser test notifications), Gulp/
#        Grunt plugins, Webpack plugins, ESLint integrations,
#        Mocha plugins, Browserify watch plugins, and basically
#        any Node.js dev-tool that wants to surface build/test
#        events to the desktop
#     9. SAFE-MESSAGE FILTERING — escapes user-supplied
#        notification content to prevent OS-level command
#        injection (especially important on macOS where AppleScript
#        is used as a fallback)
#    10. MAINTAINER — Mikael Brevik (mikaelbr) is a Norwegian
#        developer + JS Coach; maintains multiple JavaScript
#        utilities + open-source projects
#
# Maintained by Mikael Brevik (mikaelbr on GitHub).  License:
